article.headline: Southeastern Louisiana 90, Millsaps 67
article.story: HAMMOND, La. (AP) -- Quennell Green and Joseph Polite led four Southeastern Louisiana players in double figures with 16 points each and the Lions shot 63.6 percent from the field in a dominating 90-67 non-conference win over Millsaps Wednesday night. Southeastern (8-4) also won the battle of the boards, outrebounding Millsaps 36-28 and had 26 assists to nine for the Majors (4-5). Daryl Cohen had 15 points for Southeastern while Terry Bryant added 14 -- all in the first half. The Lions' 90 point tally was a season high along with the field goal percentage as the squad hit 35-of-55 attempts including 9-of-20 (45 percent) from behind the arc. Edrick Montgomery led Millsaps with a game-high 17 points on 7-of-14 aim while Lorenzo Bailey chipped in 15 and Allen Odum added 13 points and three assists. Southeastern scored 53 first half points in building a commanding 53-35 lead at the break led by Bryant's 14 points on a 6-of-8 first-half aim. Millsaps made a run in the second half, cutting the Lions' advantage to 11 points twice, the last on a jumper by Montgomery at the 13:17 mark. But Southeastern answered with a 13-4 run over the next 4:09 to increase the lead to 20 points, 75-55, and essentially salt the game away.
